        "caption": "List of stars identified as highly-likely runaway stars by the method described in Sec. \\ref{sec:principal}. $P_{\\mathrm{run}}$ is the probability that the star is a runaway, $v_{\\mathrm{run}}$ is the posterior runaway velocity and $d$ is the posterior distance inferred from the parallax. All of the names are resolvable by Simbad. The starred entries are high-peculiar space velocity stars mentioned by \\citet{berger_search_2001}. Based on Fig. \\ref{fig:roccurve}, we should expect around 4 of these stars to be false positives.",
